_id.title: Identifier
_id.description: A unique identifier for the time-series event.

timestamp.title: Timestamp
timestamp.description: The time when an event or observation occurred.

eventType.title: Event Type
eventType.description: The primary event type for this time-series record.

meta:enum.advertising.completes: Indicates if a timed media asset was watched to completion - this does not necessarily mean the viewer watched the whole video; viewer could have skipped ahead.
meta:enum.advertising.timePlayed: Describes the amount of time spent by a user on a specific timed media asset.
meta:enum.advertising.federated: Indicates if an experience event was created through data federation (data sharing between customers).
meta:enum.advertising.conversions: A customer pre-defined action(s) which triggers an event for performance evaluation.
meta:enum.advertising.firstQuartiles: A digital video ad has played through 25% of its duration at normal speed.
meta:enum.advertising.impressions: Impression(s) of an advertisement to an end-user with the potential of being viewed.
meta:enum.advertising.midpoints: A digital video ad has played through 50% of its duration at normal speed.
meta:enum.advertising.starts: A digital video ad has started playing.
meta:enum.advertising.thirdQuartiles: A digital video ad has played through 75% of its duration at normal speed.
meta:enum.web.webpagedetails.pageViews: View(s) of a webpage has occurred.
meta:enum.web.webinteraction.linkClicks: Click of a web-link has occurred.
meta:enum.commerce.checkouts: An action during a checkout process of a product list, there can be more than one checkout event if there are multiple steps in a checkout process. If there are multiple steps the event time information and referenced page or experience is used to identify the step individual events represent in order.
meta:enum.commerce.productListAdds: Addition of a product to the product list. Example a product is added to a shopping cart.
meta:enum.commerce.productListOpens: Initializations of a new product list. Example a shopping cart is created.
meta:enum.commerce.productListRemovals: Removal(s) of a product entry from a product list. Example a product is removed from a shopping cart.
meta:enum.commerce.productListReopens: A product list that was no longer accessible(abandoned) has been re-activated by the user. Example via a re-marketing activity.
meta:enum.commerce.productListViews: View(s) of a product-list has occurred.
meta:enum.commerce.productViews: View(s) of a product have occurred.
meta:enum.commerce.purchases: An order has been accepted. Purchase is the only required action in a commerce conversion. Purchase must have a product list referenced.
meta:enum.commerce.saveForLaters: Product list is saved for future use. Example a product wish list.

message.title: A single message sent to a recipient.

profileSnapshot.title: Profile Snapshot
profileSnapshot.description: Profile snapshot contains the recipient of the message. This property is primarily used to link the message to a Profile using the `IdentityMap` but it can also be used to freeze some properties of the profile at the time the message was sent.

homeAddress.title: Address
homeAddress.description: A postal address. Address could relate to a person's home, work, preferred store location etc.

_id.title: Coordinates ID
_id.description: The unique identifier of the coordinates.

description.title: Description
description.description: A description of what the coordinates identify.

latitude.title: Latitude
latitude.description: The signed vertical coordinate of a geographic point.

longitude.title: Longitude
longitude.description: The signed horizontal coordinate of a geographic point.

elevation.title: Elevation
elevation.description: The specific elevation of the defined coordinate. The value conforms to the [WGS84](http://gisgeography.com/wgs84-world-geodetic-system/) datum and is measured in meters.

countryCode.title: Country code
countryCode.description: The two-character [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2](https://datahub.io/core/country-list) code for the country.

stateProvince.title: State or province
stateProvince.description: The state, or province portion of the observation. The format follows the [ISO 3166-2 (country and subdivision)][http://www.unece.org/cefact/locode/subdivisions.html] standard.

postalCode.title: Postal code
postalCode.description: The postal code of the location. Postal codes are not available for all countries. In some countries, this will only contain part of the postal code.

dmaID.title: Designated Market Area
dmaID.description: The Nielsen media research designated market area.

msaID.title: Metropolitan Statistical Area
msaID.description: The metropolitan statistical area in the USA where the observation occurred.

repositoryCreatedBy.title: Created by User Identifier
repositoryCreatedBy.description: User ID who has created the entity.

repositoryLastModifiedBy.title: Modified by User Identifier
repositoryLastModifiedBy.description: User ID who last modified the entity. At creation time, `modifiedByUser` is set as `createdByUser`.

createdByBatchID.title: Created by Batch Identifier
createdByBatchID.description: The dataset files in Catalog Services which has been originating the creation of the entity.

modifiedByBatchID.title: Modified by Batch Identifier
modifiedByBatchID.description: The last dataset files in Catalog Services which has modified the entity. At creation time, `modifiedByBatchID` is set as `createdByBatchID`.

createDate.description: The server date and time when the resource was created in the repository, such as when an asset file is first uploaded or a directory is created by the server as the parent of a new asset. The date time property should conform to ISO 8601 standard. An example form is "2004-10-23T12:00:00-06:00".

modifyDate.description: The server date and time when the resource was last modified in the repository, such as when a new version of an asset is uploaded or a directory's child resource is added or removed. The date time property should conform to ISO 8601 standard. An example form is "2004-10-23T12:00:00-06:00".

primary.title: Primary
primary.description: Primary address indicator. A profile can have only one `primary` address at a given point of time.

label.title: Label
label.description: Free form name of the address.

street1.title: Street 1
street1.description: Primary Street level information, apartment number, street number and street name.

region.title: Region
region.description: The region, county, or district portion of the address.

postOfficeBox.title: Post Office Box
postOfficeBox.description: Post office box of the address.

country.title: Country
country.description: The name of the government-administered territory. Other than `xdm:countryCode`, this is a free-form field that can have the country name in any language.

status.title: Status
status.description: An indication as to the ability to use the address.

statusReason.title: Status Reason
statusReason.description: A description of the current status.

lastVerifiedDate.title: Last Verified Date
lastVerifiedDate.description: The date that the address was last verified as still belonging to the person.

primary.title: Primary
primary.description:
Primary email indicator.

A Profile can have only one `primary` email address at a given point of time.

address.title: Address
address.description: The technical address, e.g 'name@domain.com' as commonly defined in RFC2822 and subsequent standards.

label.title: Label
label.description: Additional display information that maybe available, e.g MS Outlook rich address controls display 'John Smith smithjr@company.uk', the 'John Smith' part is data that would be placed in the label.

type.title: Type
type.description: The way the account relates to the person. e.g 'work' or 'personal'

status.title: Status
status.description: An indication as to the ability to use the email address.

statusReason.title: Status Reason
statusReason.description: A description of the current status.

homePhone.title: Phone Number
homePhone.description: Information that allows the phone calling of a person. Typically an alphanumeric number, 1-222-333 4444 in North America, but can have a wide range of formats.

primary.title: Primary
primary.description:
Primary phone number indicator.

Unlike for Address or EmailAddress, there can be multiple primary phone numbers; one per communication channel.
The communication channel is defined by the type:

* `textMessaging`: type = `mobile`
* `phone`: type = `home` | `work` | `unknown`
* `fax`: type = `fax`

number.title: Number
number.description: The phone number. Note the phone number is a string and may include meaningful characters such as brackets (), hyphens - or characters to indicate sub dialing identifiers like extensions x. E.g 1-353(0)18391111 or +613 9403600x1234.

extension.title: Extension
extension.description: The internal dialing number used to call from a private exchange, operator or switchboard.

status.title: Status
status.description: An indication as to the ability to use the phone number.

statusReason.title: Status Reason
statusReason.description: A description of the current status.

validity.title: Validity
validity.description: A level of technical correctness of the phone number.

num.title: Session Number
num.description: Current session number for the end-user.

depth.title: Session Depth
depth.description: Current session depth (eg page number) for the end-user.

timestamp.title: Session Entry Timestamp
timestamp.description: The timestamp at the entry into this session. Milliseconds since midnight of January 1, 1970.

searchEngine.title: Search Engine
searchEngine.description: The search engine used by the search.

searchEngineID.title: Search Engine ID
searchEngineID.description: The application-specified identifier used to identify the search engine used by the search.

isPaid.title: Is Paid
isPaid.description: Indicate if the search is paid or not.

pageDepth.title: Page Depth
pageDepth.description: Page depth in the search results.

slot.title: Page Slot
slot.description: Named section of the page where the search result appeared. For eg. Top, Side.

position.title: Listing Position
position.description: Position (rank) of the listing in the search result page.

siteSection.title: Site Section
siteSection.description: The normative name of the site section where this web page resides, which may be used to classify or categorize the interaction.

name.title: Name
name.description: The normative name of the web page. This name is not necessarily the page title or directly associate with page content, but is used to organize a site's pages for classification purposes.

URL.title: URL
URL.description: The normative or usual URL of the web page.  This may or may not be the actual URL used to reach the page, which would be recorded using `Web Link`.

server.title: Server
server.description: The normative or usual server that hosts the web page.  This may or may not be the host or server that actually served the page interaction, but is used for classification purposes.

isErrorPage.title: Is Error Page
isErrorPage.description: Flag that indicate if the page is error page or not.  Error here is defined by the application, and may nor may not correspond to a page served with an HTTP error code.  This flag is used to broadly categorize web interactions.

isHomePage.title: Is Home Page
isHomePage.description: Flag that indicate if the page is the site home page or not.  The definition of home page is determined by the application, but is commonly used to designate a top level landing page or common site entry point.  This flag is used to broadly categorize web interactions.

id.title: Unique Identifier
id.description: Unique identifier of the measure. In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

value.description: The quantifiable value of this measure.

id.title: Unique Identifier
id.description: Unique identifier of the measure. In cases of data collection using lossy communication channels, such as mobile apps or websites with offline functionality, where transmission of measures cannot be ensured, this property contains a client-generated, unique ID of the measure taken. It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

It is best practice to make this sufficiently long to ensure enough entropy. Additionally, if information such as time stamp, device ID, IP, or MAC address, or other potentially user-identifying values are incorporated in the generation of the xdm:id, the result should be hashed, so that no PII is encoded in the value, as the goal is not to identify user or device, but the specific measure in time.

value.description: The quantifiable value of this measure.
